---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Professional Athletes | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Professional Athletes working internationally, covering sports positions abroad, athletic careers, and global professional sports opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Professional Athletes";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Professional Athletes working abroad, competing internationally, and pursuing careers across global sports organizations.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/professional-athlete-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/professional-athlete-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Professional Athlete Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Professional Athletes compete at elite levels in their sports—playing for teams, representing countries, or competing individually across global competitions. International athletic careers offer opportunities to play in top leagues worldwide, experience diverse sporting cultures, and develop expertise at the highest levels of competition.
      </p>
      <p>
        International athletic opportunities exist through professional leagues, national teams, individual competition circuits, and sports organizations globally.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Professional Athletes working abroad across global sports organizations.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Professional Athletes</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'Sports injury coverage', why: 'Athletic injury frequency', typical: 'Usually team-provided' },
          { need: 'Orthopedic specialty', why: 'Joint and muscle injuries', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Rehabilitation coverage', why: 'Recovery requirements', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Loss of career', why: 'Career-ending injury risk', typical: 'Critical for athletes' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Performance pressure', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Competition travel', typical: 'Often included' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Injury Reality</h3>
      <p>
        Professional sports involve inherent injury risk—muscle tears, joint injuries, fractures, and concussions are occupational hazards. A single injury can sideline an athlete for months. Career-ending injuries happen. Comprehensive sports injury and orthopedic coverage is essential for athletic careers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Loss of career insurance protects athletes against injuries that end competitive careers.
      </p>

      <h3>Performance Pressure</h3>
      <p>
        Elite athletics involves intense psychological demands—performance expectations, competition stress, media scrutiny, and career uncertainty. Mental health challenges are common in professional sports. Support for the psychological aspects of athletic performance protects both career and wellbeing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Professional Team</h3>
      <p>
        League team. Team-provided coverage. Medical staff access. Teams offer comprehensive care.
      </p>

      <h3>National Team</h3>
      <p>
        International representation. Federation coverage. Competition focus. National teams offer support.
      </p>

      <h3>Individual Sport</h3>
      <p>
        Tennis, golf, athletics. Self-provided often. Competition earnings. Individual requires planning.
      </p>

      <h3>Combat Sports</h3>
      <p>
        Boxing, MMA, wrestling. Promoter coverage varies. High risk. Combat requires special attention.
      </p>

      <h3>Extreme Sports</h3>
      <p>
        Action sports. Sponsor coverage varies. Specialty risks. Extreme requires specialty coverage.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Professional Athletes"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Professional Athletes working abroad across global sports organizations."
      buttonText="Compare Athletic Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Athletic Performance</h3>
      <p>
        Competitive results. Career statistics. Recognition. Performance speaks.
      </p>

      <h3>Contract Status</h3>
      <p>
        Team contracts. Sponsorship agreements. Federation registration. Contracts formalize status.
      </p>

      <h3>Ranking/Standing</h3>
      <p>
        World rankings. League position. Career achievements. Rankings demonstrate level.
      </p>

      <h3>Agent Representation</h3>
      <p>
        Professional representation. Contract negotiation. Career management. Agents enable business.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Injury Risk</h3>
      <p>
        Sports injuries. Acute trauma. Overuse conditions. Sports injury coverage essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Recovery</h3>
      <p>
        Rehabilitation needs. Return protocols. Performance restoration. Rehab coverage critical.
      </p>

      <h3>Mental Health</h3>
      <p>
        Performance pressure. Career stress. Identity challenges. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Long-Term Effects</h3>
      <p>
        Cumulative damage. Joint wear. Neurological concerns. Comprehensive coverage important.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Training</h3>
      <p>
        Physical preparation. Skill development. Tactical work. Training enables performance.
      </p>

      <h3>Competition</h3>
      <p>
        Competitive events. Performance execution. Results achievement. Competition is the goal.
      </p>

      <h3>Recovery</h3>
      <p>
        Physical recovery. Injury rehabilitation. Mental restoration. Recovery sustains career.
      </p>

      <h3>Business</h3>
      <p>
        Contract management. Sponsorship obligations. Media requirements. Business supports career.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Limited Duration</h3>
      <p>
        Athletic prime short. Career window limited. Transition inevitable. Duration reality.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Coaching. Media. Business. Administration. Post-career paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        Athletic skills specific. Competition experience valued. Name recognition transfers. Skills context-dependent.
      </p>

      <h3>Field Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        Sports science advances. Technology integration. Global expansion. Field evolving continuously.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a professional athlete considering international play. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Teams typically provide coverage. Injury treatment included. Personal coverage supplements. Verify contract details.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do teams provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Professional teams typically yes. Medical staff available. Comprehensive usually. Contract specifies coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is loss of career insurance important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Critical for athletes. Career-ending injuries happen. Financial protection essential. Priority coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do athletic credentials transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Performance speaks universally. Competition experience transfers. Adaptation needed. Skills demonstrate.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is mental health support important for athletes?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes increasingly recognized. Performance pressure significant. Career stress real. Mental health support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Competitive always. Limited positions. International opportunities growing. Outlook depends on sport.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating team or federation coverage. Prioritize loss of career insurance for injury protection. Ensure comprehensive rehabilitation coverage. Consider mental health support for performance demands.
      </p>
      <p>
        Professional Athletes compete at elite levels worldwide. Your coverage should support athletic careers—addressing injury risks and performance demands, covering rehabilitation and recovery, and protecting you across global sports competitions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Athletic Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Professional Athletes working abroad across global sports organizations."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
